 and Operations personnel as not to disrupt facility processes. Locates and purchases equipment and tools necessary to perform all maintenance activities. Locates and schedules equipment consultants and engineers for repair and replacement projects.\nGraduation from an accredited high school or possession of an acceptable equivalency diploma is required.\nMechanic I -At least 12 months previous experience in an appropriate craft or trade.Will be required to pass a basic mechanical knowledge test to be moved from Entry Level Probation to Regular employee status. State of Florida driver's license.\nMechanic II \u2013AfterSuccessful completion of Mechanic I requirements with two (2) years on the job training. Must have completed the following technical courses and tests: Elements of Mechanics; Basic Pneumatics; Basic Hydraulics; Bearings; Lubrication. Will be required to complete a practical exam to include the following: Disassemble and reassemble a training rotating assembly; Recite 1/16 incremental measurements to one inch; Disassemble and reassemble a training gear box. Will be encouraged to obtain a Class \"C\" State of Florida Wastewater certification. State of Florida Class \"A\" CDL required.\nMechanic III \u2013after serving twelve (36) months as a WD Mechanic Il, provided he/she: Has demonstrated that he/she has a clear and demonstrable understanding of all the requirements of the position and has received satisfactory annual evaluations; must complete all five workbooks drive components, piping systems, pneumatic trouble shooting, hydraulic trouble shooting and pumps; must complete and pass practical exam.\nTraining courses in repair of mechanical equipment. Two years' experience in operation, maintenance and repair of Wastewater equipment. Must have completed the following technical courses: Drive Components; Piping Systems; Pneumatic Trouble Shooting; Hydraulic Trouble Shooting; Pumps. Will be strongly encouraged to obtain a Class \"C\" State of Florida Wa