 and energy usage to ensure compliance with applicable codes, ordinances, and regulations; checks to see that buildings and structures are being constructed in accordance with approved plans, specifications, and energy calculations; ensures that proper quality building materials are being used; identifies and ensures correction of defects in construction work, including electrical, plumbing, mechanical, concrete, framework, masonry, lathing, plastering, and tile construction; explains and interprets applicable codes and ordinances for contractors and the general public; approves issue of building permits; may check some plans for residential structures, preparing lists of corrections; performs inspections of existing structures to identify potential safety and structural failures, and alteration needs; issues notices of non-compliance with safe structural requirements and applicable ordinances; maintains records and reports of inspections; prepares correspondence; investigates citizen and tenant complaints regarding code violations; provides general information about structural and code requirements to interested individuals; collects monies and fees for licenses and permits; may coordinate inspection assignments with other County departments and government agencies; works cooperatively with other departments on common inspections; and keeps apprised of applicable ordinances related to departmental projects. OTHER JOB RELATED DUTIESPerforms related duties and responsibilities as assigned.\n\nMINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS\nKnowledge of: Basic principles, methods, and techniques used in building inspection.Modern methods of building construction.Types of building materials and variations in their quality.Level II Also Requires: Pertinent Federal, State, and local laws, codes, ordinances, and regulations related to building construction and structural requirements.Acceptable health, safety, and fire standards in building construction.Skill to: Operate a motor vehicle safely.A