ation activities. Work at the fire station and scenes of fires, is normally performed under close supervision in accordance with well-defined procedures, and is supervised by a Fire Captain. Occasionally, employees in this class may be required to relieve an Driver/Engineer and will be capable of performing all job functions listed in Driver/Engineer job description. Firefighters may be assigned to work on special assignments which call for special abilities and knowledge attained through experience and training.\n\nEXAMPLE OF DUTIES\nESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS: Demonstrates superior seamless customer service, integrity, and commitment to innovation, efficiency, fiscally responsible activity, and adhere to the principal of Finish the Call. Lays and connects hose, holds nozzles and directs water streams, raises and climbs ladders, use various types of fire extinguishers, use Haligan bars, hooks, ropes, and other equipment at emergency scenes; Performs salvage operations; Administers EMS to injured persons, frequently using advance techniques to restore cardio-pulmonary functions; Participates in fire drills and attends classes in firefighting, EMS and related duties; Performs general maintenance work in the up-keep of the Fire Department property; Inspects commercial and noncommercial buildings; Participate in and complete Pre-Fire Plans of commercial and target hazard structures Attends public gatherings to ensure observance of fire safety requirements; Participates in station radio tests; Perform various Public Education classes to help promote fire safety within the community. Conducts tours of station houses for scout, civic and other interested groups; Maintains regular and reliable attendance. Will be required to demonstrate knowledge of fire district to include streets, hydrant locations, sprinkler connections, types of building construction, and any hazard areas located within their assigned district. Must respond to Mutual Aid request from neighboring departments. 